    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A type of heavy paper composed of rags impregnated with asphalt; used in the manufacture of waterproofing membranes, and for making asphalt shingles and other types of composition roofing, such as asphalt roofing.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000033931/Putnam and Carlson, Architectural and Building Trades Dictionary (1974)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tipo de papel pesado compuesto de trapos impregnados de asfalto y utilizado en la fabricación de membranas impermeables y para fabricar tejas de asfalto y otros tipos de material de techumbre, tal como la techumbre de asfalto.
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een zware papiersoort bestaande uit lompen die zijn geïmpregneerd met asfalt; wordt gebruikt voor het maken van waterdichte membranen, asfaltdakspanen en andere soorten samengestelde dakbedekking zoals bitumineuze dakbedekking.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
